
zombie - a process that has exited but stays in the process table as a PID and exit status.
it's there until it's still-living parent calls wait() to collect it.

a zombie and <defunct> are the same thing

orphan - a still running process whoae parent died so it gets adopted by PID 1 (init) which
will reap it when it eventually exits. 


zombie - the child died and is waiting to be collected. 

orphan - the parent died and the living child got re-homed. 
